race.comment: AGARWOOD (3) above average filly who graduated quickly to Group company last prep. Stalked the fast tempo first-up with a game second as fav over 1100m at this track. Comes to hand quickly and the 3kg claim can offset the sticky draw. Expected to go close. FERINZO (6) sharp Gosford-trained gelding who keeps raising the bar on the provincial circuit. Comes to town for the first time after he rounded up inferior opposition in good style over 1100m at Gosford. Gets the right run and will have no problem running out the 1250m. ALBANY ROAD (4) is undefeated in his last three outings and stretches out to this trip for the first time. Defeated a handy field when he got up late over 1100m at this track. Should be able to get cover from the draw and take a hand in the finish. SLINKY (7) on the quick backup after closing fast for a respectable fifth over 1250m at this track last Friday night. Anywhere near her best could win this.
